<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
This species was described based on a single female specimen only. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" author="Wilkinson, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 517" refId="B26" refString="Wilkinson, C, 1968. A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 31 (4): 407 - 517, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" title="A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" volume="31" year="1968">Wilkinson (1968)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the female genitalia are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona legnichrysa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="legnichrysa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona legnichrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson, and he also had difficulty in distinguishing it from 
<taxonomicName family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. legnichrysa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="legnichrysa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. legnichrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, though he listed several tiny differences. He suggested that further material was needed to clarify the relationship between the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
